    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i guess the \"innovation\" thing sounds good on paper but for a shop with like 10 employees, isn't it mostly just about the cost of staying afloat? like, are there actually any real documented cases where these rules helped small businesses economically, or is it mostly just a burden?",
